We are happy to announce that the 24x7 Toll-Free Tourist Infoline implemented by the Ministry of Tourism, Government of India has successfully completed one year of service. The Multilingual Infoline seeks to make tourism a safe & hassle-free experience for domestic and international tourists. The helpline provides tourists information relating to Travel & Tourism in India and also assist the callers by recommending the actions that need to be taken during times of distress while travelling in India.

With its forested hills, tranquil beaches and the Chikoo orchards, Dahanu is a place of great picturesque charm. Every year a two-day Chikoo Festival is organized in Dahanu, Maharashtra. The festival features local dancers, workshops, food stalls, farm visits and much more. 

So, go chikoo picking in the orchards and get yourself baskets of grapefruits, chikoos and loads of colourful memories on your way home.

#Dahanu #Maharashtra #Chikoo #IncredibleIndia

Have you ever dreamt of spending a cosy, romantic evening in a city that seems straight out of a picture-story book? Then, head to Gangtok, and rekindle your love in its picturesque surroundings. With snow-covered mountains, a fascinating variety of flora & fauna and beautiful parks & gardens, Gangtok will surely woo your senses. And what’s more, there is nothing more beautiful than experiencing the magnificent sunrise over the Kanchenjunga while cuddling up with your loved one. Truly romantic, right?

#RomanticGetaway #Gangtok #IncredibleIndia

An amazing structure!

The Deeg Palace or ‘Jal Mahal’, situated 32 km north of Bharatpur, is renowned for its architectural magnificence. The palace showcases a confluence of Mughal and Rajput architecture and is the perfect destination for lovers of art and history. With its splendid gardens, marble fountains and beautiful water designs, which simulate the rains and clouds, the palace is sure to captivate your senses. 

#Rajasthan #IncredibleIndia
